		<div class="js-mul-tabs-example mul-tabs">
			{% include "page-tabs" %}
			<div id="tabs-1">
				<p>The Tooltip feature provides the user additional information/detail on <a href="form-input">Form Input</a> fields that is not initially displayed. This additional information displayed with the Tooltip shouldn't be crucial, required functionality, content needed to interact with the interface. It is simply a bit of additional information that would be considered helpful to the user, not essential.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-2">
				<p>Designers should use the Tooltip when the amount of information displayed is short in length (10-15 words maximum) and not critical to the user. For longer content (more than 15 words or images) use the <a href="comp-descriptive-hover">Descriptive Hover</a>.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-3">
				<strong>Text</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The designer should use concise language in the Tooltip, no more than 15 words.</li>
					<li>The Tooltip must be plain text. </li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Height/Width</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Tooltip has a maximum width of 200 pixels but can be smaller based on content.</li>
					<li>The height of the Tooltip should be dynamic and based on the content included.</li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Color</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Tooltip container should have a light blue (#e7f0f9) color background.</li>
					<li>The Tooltip container should have a light gray (#cccccc) border color.</li>
					<li>The Tooltip text will be dark gray (#333333).</li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Placement</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Tooltip's placement relative to the link should be dynamic, based on how much space is available.</li>
					<li>By default, the Tooltip should display above the link. However, if there is limited space, it should be able to dynamically shift to the bottom.</li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Accessibility</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Tooltip container will open when the user mouses over the parent element and will disappear when the user moves the mouse away from the parent element.</li>
				</ul>

			</div>
			<div id="tabs-4">
				<strong>Cross browser compatibility</strong>
				<p>IE9 doesn't crop background gradients on containers with rounded corners, so we square the corners of every container so it looks just like IE8.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

